.TH KIRO-AUDIT 8 "2026-05-28" "Kiro" "Kiro System Tools"
.SH NAME
kiro-audit \- comprehensive post-install audit of a Kiro system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kiro-audit
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kiro-audit
performs a structured PASS/WARN/FAIL audit of a Kiro system after installation.
It prints a summary with totals and exits non-zero if any check fails.
.PP
Checks performed:
.IP \(bu 4
Kernel: installed kernel(s) detected at runtime via /usr/lib/modules/*/pkgbase (linux-lqx, linux-zen, linux-hardened, ...); vmlinuz, initramfs, package, and headers verified per kernel
.IP \(bu 4
Microcode: correct vendor image in /boot, opposite vendor not installed
.IP \(bu 4
mkinitcpio: no archiso hook, microcode and kms hooks present, per-kernel mkinitcpio preset exists
.IP \(bu 4
Audio: PipeWire stack complete, pulseaudio absent
.IP \(bu 4
Calamares cleanup: calamares, mkinitcpio-archiso, and live-only artifacts removed
.IP \(bu 4
kiro_final config: /root permissions, sudoers, makepkg.conf, Bluetooth AutoEnable
.IP \(bu 4
Pacman repos: nemesis_repo and chaotic-aur present, cachyos commented out in pacman.conf
.IP \(bu 4
Desktop: ohmychadwm and xfwm4 installed, session desktop files present
.IP \(bu 4
SDDM: installed, enabled, edu-simplicity theme set
.IP \(bu 4
Kiro Plasma (only when Plasma is installed): for each installed kiro-plasma-* package, the config it ships under /etc/xdg and /etc/skel is present, and the UID 1000 user's effective settings (cursor, colour scheme, icons, widget style, window decoration) match the active Kiro look-and-feel
.IP \(bu 4
User groups: UID 1000 user in wheel, audio, video, storage, optical, network
.IP \(bu 4
Services: NetworkManager, sddm, bluetooth enabled; pacman-init not enabled
.IP \(bu 4
Permissions: /etc/shadow and /etc/gshadow at 400
.IP \(bu 4
ISO version: /etc/dev-rel present
.IP \(bu 4
NVIDIA: driver and utils installed only when GPU is detected
.IP \(bu 4
Bootloader: correct for UEFI or BIOS
.IP \(bu 4
Package integrity: no missing files (pacman -Qk)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a help message and exit (does not require root).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version information and exit (does not require root).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All checks passed (or warnings only).
.TP
.B 1
One or more checks failed, or insufficient privileges.
.SH NOTES
Must be run as root:
.B sudo kiro-audit
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kiro-verify (8),
.BR pacman (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Erik Dubois <https://www.erikdubois.be>
